annotationA: Moesin/ezrin/radixin homolog 1; Involved in connections of major cytoskeletal structures to the plasma membrane. Together with wgn, involved in control of axon targeting of R8 and R2-R5 photoreceptors, independent of egr. In the nucleus, recruited to sites of active transcription by RNA polymerase II where it has a role in nuclear mRNA export together with the mRNA export factor PCID2 and other messenger ribonucleoprotein (mRNP) particles
annotationB: Veli, isoform C; It is involved in the biological process described with: border follicle cell migration; regulation of synaptic growth at neuromuscular junction; establishment or maintenance of cell polarity
